<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10392448>
    dc:description "FIGURES 78–84. Neobisium (N.) patrizii Beier, 1953, male, Grotta di Colle Cantocchio (Bassiano, Latium). 78, epistome of carapace and right ocular area; 79, right chelicera, dorsal view; 80, anterior processes of left coxa I; 81, trochanter, femur and patella of right pedipalp, dorsal view; 82, right pedipalpal chela, dorsal view; 83, same, antiaxial view, with magnified detail of teeth; 84, right leg IV, antiaxial view, with magnified detail of subterminal seta of telotarsus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10392448/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10275970>
    dc:description "FIGURE 119. Map depicting known distribution of Neobisum species with troglomorphic facies from central and southern Italy." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10275970/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

